'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Ural'''||align=center|'''2 &ndash; 2'''||'''West'''\n|-\n|27 September 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Dacia'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 3'''||'''West'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Ural'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 3'''||'''Piedmont'''\n|}\n\n=== Group 9 ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=225 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals for\" |GF\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals against\" |GA\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goal difference\" |GD\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Ticino}} [[2. Liga (Switzerland)|Ticino]]\n|3||3||0||0||8||3||+5||'''9'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|BIH}} [[Bosnia and Herzegovina|Entity]]\n|3||2||0||1||10||4||+6||'''6'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon image|MS_flag.svg}} [[MNZ Murska Sobota]] selection\n|3||1||0||2||2||6||&minus;4||'''3'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|LIE}} [[Liechtenstein Football Association|Liechtenstein]]\n|3||0||0||3||2||9||&minus;7||'''0'''\n|}\n\n{|width=100% cellspacing=1\n!width=25%|\n!width=10%|\n!\n|-\n|17 September 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''MNZ Murska Sobota selection'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 1'''||'''Ticino'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Liechtenstein'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 4'''||'''Entity'''\n|-\n|19 September 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''MNZ Murska Sobota selection'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 4'''||'''Entity'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Liechtenstein'''||align=center|'''1 &ndash; 3'''||'''Ticino'''\n|-\n|21 September 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''MNZ Murska Sobota selection'''||align=center|'''2 &ndash; 1'''||'''Liechtenstein'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Ticino'''||align=center|'''4 &ndash; 2'''||'''Entity'''\n|}\n\n=== Group 10 ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals for\" |GF\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals against\" |GA\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goal difference\" |GD\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|- bgcolor=#ccccff\n|align=left|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Gothenburg Football Association|Gothenburg]]\n|3||2||1||0||5||0||+5||'''7'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|LVA}} [[Latvian Football Federation|Latvia]]\n|3||1||2||0||2||1||+1||'''5'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|IRL}} [[Football Association of Ireland|Republic of Ireland]]\n|3||1||0||2||4||2||+2||'''3'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Strathclyde|West Scotland]]\n|3||0||1||2||1||9||&minus;8||'''1'''\n|}\n\n{|width=100% cellspacing=1\n!width=25%|\n!width=10%|\n!\n|-\n|8 October 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Latvia'''||align=center|'''1 &ndash; 1'''||'''West Scotland'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Republic of Ireland'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 1'''||'''Gothenburg'''\n|-\n|10 October 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Republic of Ireland'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 1'''||'''Latvia'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''West Scotland'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 4'''||'''Gothenburg'''\n|-\n|12 October 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''West Scotland'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 4'''||'''Republic of Ireland'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Latvia'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 0'''||'''Gothenburg'''\n|}\n\n== Intermediary round ==\nThe intermediary [[playoff]]s were drawn at random when the preliminary groups were drawn. As there were ten groups but only eight places in the final tournament, four group winners had to play in the intermediary round. The winners of Group 2 were drawn to play the winners of Group 4, whilst Group 8 and Group 10's winners would play each other. The two legs were played in both competing teams' home regions.\n\n{{TwoLeg start}}\n{{TwoLegResult |'''[[Piedmont]]'''|Piedmont|2&ndash;0|[[Gothenburg Football Association|Gothenburg]]|SWE|1&ndash;0|1&ndash;0}}\n{{TwoLegResult |[[Bohemian Football League|Bohemia]]|Bohemia|0&ndash;2|'''[[Royal Football Federation of the Principality of Asturias|Asturias]]'''|Asturias|0&ndash;1|0&ndash;1}}\n|}\n\n'''First legs'''\n{|width=100% cellspacing=1\n!width=25%|\n!width=10%|\n!\n|-\n|19 March 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Piedmont'''||align=center|'''1 &ndash; 0'''||'''Gothenburg'''\n|-\n|16 April 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Bohemia'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 1'''||'''Asturias'''\n|}\n\n'''Second legs'''\n{|width=100% cellspacing=1\n!width=25%|\n!width=10%|\n!\n|-\n|9 April 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Gothenburg'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 1'''||'''Piedmont'''\n|-\n|7 May 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Asturias'''||align=center|'''1 &ndash; 0'''||'''Bohemia'''\n|}\n\n== Final tournament ==\n[[Germany]] was chosen to host the final tournament, with matches being played from 22 June to 28 June 2003.\n\n=== Group stage ===\nThe six automatic preliminary group winners and the two intermediary playoff winners ([[Italy]]'s ''[[Piedmont]]'' and ''[[Royal Football Federation of the Principality of Asturias|Asturias]]'' of [[Spain]]) were drawn into two groups of four, with the two group winners advancing to the final.\n\n==== Group A ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals for\" |GF\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals against\" |GA\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goal difference\" |GD\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Piedmont}} [[Piedmont]]\n|3||2||1||0||7||2||+5||'''7'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon image|Flagge_K\u00f6nigreich_W\u00fcrttemberg.svg}} [[W\u00fcrttemberg Football Association|W\u00fcrttemberg]]\n|3||1||1||1||6||4||+2||'''4'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Ticino}} [[2. Liga (Switzerland)|Ticino]]\n|3||1||0||2||1||7||&minus;6||'''3'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon image|Flag_of_Asturias.svg}} [[Royal Football Federation of the Principality of Asturias|Asturias]]\n|3||0||2||1||2||3||&minus;1||'''2'''\n|}\n\n{|width=100% cellspacing=1\n!width=25%|\n!width=10%|\n!\n|-\n|22 June 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''W\u00fcrttemberg'''||align=center|'''4 &ndash; 0'''||'''Ticino'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Asturias'''||align=center|'''1 &ndash; 1'''||'''Piedmont'''\n|-\n|24 June 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Ticino'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 3'''||'''Piedmont'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''W\u00fcrttemberg'''||align=center|'''1 &ndash; 1'''||'''Asturias'''\n|-\n|26 June 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Ticino'''||align=center|'''1 &ndash; 0'''||'''Asturias'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Piedmont'''||align=center|'''3 &ndash; 1'''||'''W\u00fcrttemberg'''\n|}\n\n==== Group B ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals for\" |GF\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals against\" |GA\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goal difference\" |GD\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n|align=left|{{flagicon image|Maine_flag.svg}} [[Maine (province)|Maine]]\n|3||2||0||1||12||6||+6||'''6'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon image|Flag-Szabolcs-Szatmar-Bereg-megye.svg}} [[Szabolcs-Szatm\u00e1r-Bereg County|Szabolcs]]\n|3||2||0||1||15||8||+7||'''6'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|NED}} [[Royal Dutch Football Association|Noord]]\n|3||1||1||1||4||9||&minus;5||'''4'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|AZE}} [[Association of Football Federations of Azerbaijan|G\u00f6yazan]]\n|3||0||1||2||5||13||&minus;8||'''1'''\n|}\n\n{|width=100% cellspacing=1\n!width=25%|\n!width=10%|\n!\n|-\n|22 June 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Szabolcs'''||align=center|'''3 &ndash; 8'''||'''Maine'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Noord'''||align=center|'''3 &ndash; 3'''||'''G\u00f6yazan'''\n|-\n|24 June 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Szabolcs'''||align=center|'''6 &ndash; 0'''||'''Noord'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Maine'''||align=center|'''4 &ndash; 2'''||'''G\u00f6yazan'''\n|-\n|26 June 2003\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''G\u00f6yazan'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 6'''||'''Szabolcs'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Maine'''||align=center|'''0 &ndash; 1'''||'''Noord ''([[wiktionary:abandon|a]])'''''\n|}\n\n=== Final ===\n{{footballbox\n|date=28 June 2003\n|time=\n|team1=[[:fr:Ligue du Maine de football|Maine]] {{flagicon image|Maine_flag.svg}}\n|score=1 &ndash; 2\n|report=[http://www.uefa.com/competitions/regionscup/history/season=2003/round=1616/index.html (Report)]\n|team2= [[Piedmont]] {{flagicon|Piedmont}}\n|goals1=Kharraz {{goal|83}}\n|goals2=Borgna {{goal|24}} {{goal|29}}\n|stadium=[[GAGFAH-Arena|Albstadion]], [[Heidenheim an der Brenz|Heidenheim]]\n|attendance=~800\n|referee=Kris Hermans ([[Royal Belgian Football Association|Belgium]]) }}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0 auto; width: 20%\"\n|-\n!2003 UEFA Regions' Cup<br />Winners\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ITA|size=50px}} [[Image:Bandiera della regione Piemonte.svg|50px|border|Piedmont]]\n|-\n|'''[[Piedmont]]'''\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n*[[UEFA Regions' Cup]]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080921224323/http://www.uefa.com/competitions/regionscup/ Official UEFA Regions' Cup site]\n*[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]] [http://www.rsssf.com/tablesu/uefa-regions03.html page for the 2003 UEFA Regions' Cup]\n\n{{UEFA Regions' Cup}}\n\n[[Category:UEFA Regions' Cup|2003]]\n[[Category:2002\u201303 in European football|Regions' Cup]]\n[[Category:International association football competitions hosted by Germany]]\n[[Category:2002\u201303 in German football|Reg]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox International Football Competition\n| tourney_name = UEFA Regions' Cup\n| year = 2003\n| other_titles = UEFA Regions' Cup Germany 2003\n| image = \n| size =\n| caption =\n| country = Germany\n| dates = 22 June &ndash; 28 June \n| num_teams = 8\n| confederations =\n| venues =\n| cities =\n| champion_other = {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Piedmont]]\n| count = 1\n| second_other = {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Maine (province)|Maine]]\n| third_other =\n| fourth_other =\n| matches =\n| goals =\n| attendance =\n| top_scorer =\n| updated =\n}}\nThe '''2003 UEFA Regions' Cup''' was the third [[UEFA Regions' Cup]]. It was held in [[Germany]] and won by the ''[[Piedmont]]'' team from [[Italy]], which beat [[France]]'s ''[[Maine (province)|Maine]]'' 2&ndash;1 in the final.\n\n== Preliminary round ==\nThe 40 teams entered were drawn into ten groups of four, with the following countries hosting each group's matches:\n:Group 1 &ndash; {{flag|Azerbaijan}}\n:Group 2 &ndash; {{flag|Belgium}}\n:Group 3 &ndash; {{flag|Croatia}}\n:Group 4 &ndash; {{flag|Estonia}}\n:Group 5 &ndash; {{flag|Hungary}}\n:Group 6 &ndash; {{flag|Lithuania}}\n:Group 7 &ndash; {{flag|Netherlands}}\n:Group 8 &ndash; {{flag|Slovakia}}\n:Group 9 &ndash; {{flag|Slovenia}}\n:Group 10 &ndash; {{flag|Sweden}}\nSix group winners qualified automatically, while the winners of four randomly drawn groups took part in a [[playoff]] for the two remaining places in the final tournament.\n\n=== Group 1 ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals for\" |GF\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals against\" |GA\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goal difference\" |GD\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|- bgcolor=#ccffcc\n|align=left|{{flagicon|AZE}} [[Qazakh Rayon|G\u00f6yazan]]\n|3||3||0||0||11||2||+9||'''9'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|UKR}} [[FC Pivdenstal Yenakiive|Pivdenstal]]\n|3||2||0||1||13||1||+12||'''6'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|GRE}} [[Imathia Football Clubs Association|Imathia]]\n|3||1||0||2||3||13||&minus;10||'''3'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon image|Flag_of_Tbilisi.svg}} [[Tbilisi]]\n|3||0||0||3||2||13||&minus;11||'''0'''\n|}\n\n{|width=100% cellspacing=1\n!width=25%|\n!width=10%|\n!\n|-\n|19 September 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Imathia'''||align=center|'''2 &ndash; 1'''||'''Tbilisi'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''G\u00f6yazan'''||align=center|'''1 &ndash; 0'''||'''Pivdenstal'''\n|-\n|21 September 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Pivdenstal'''||align=center|'''7 &ndash; 0'''||'''Imathia'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Tbilisi'''||align=center|'''1 &ndash; 5'''||'''G\u00f6yazan'''\n|-\n|23 September 2002\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''Pivdenstal'''||align=center|'''6 &ndash; 0'''||'''Tbilisi'''\n|- style=font-size:90%\n|align=right|'''G\u00f6yazan'''||align=center|'''5 &ndash; 1'''||'''Imathia'''\n|}\n\n=== Group 2 ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals for\" |GF\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goals against\" |GA\n!width=20 abbr=\"Goal difference\" |GD\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|- bgcolor=#ccccff\n|align=left|{{flagicon image|Flag_of_Asturias.svg}} [[Royal Football Federation of the Principality of Asturias|Asturias]]\n|3||3||0||0||13||0||+13||'''9'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|BEL}} Noord\n|3||2||0||1||9||3||+6||'''6'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|AND}} [[Andorran Football Federation|Andorra]]\n|3||1||0||2||2||12||&minus;10||'''3'''\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|FIN}} [[South Karelia|South-East]]\n|3||0||0||3||3||12||&minus;9||'''0'''\n|}\n\n{|width=100% cellspacing=1\n!width=25%|\n!width=10%|\n!\n|-\n|